caption: I have ordered twice thru Seamless and Faro never disappoints. The quality and flavor are exceptional.  Best Italian in Brooklyn!

If you are seeking a restaurant that is always going to wow you, send you on an adventure that is always going to end with delicious food - perhaps with just a few ingredients that personally feel out of reach but surprise you into being amazing this is the meal. The food encompasses farm to table in decor and every single element, blending northern Italian pleasantries with hearty American faire. Always get the bread and butter, always get whatever the dessert is that is served in a cup, both will always be different and delicious. Go on a pasta adventure, try the thing you aren’t confident in, or go for the old standby bucatini that will never disappoint.  I am a self proclaimed die hard fan of chef Kevin and Deb, who have been feeding me for about 10 years now and Chef has never made a dish I truly didn’t enjoy. I will always return here first upon coming home, and find any excuse to make a meal at faro.  Endlessly smitten.

Came here with two other friends so we can order a lot from the menu, the starters while beautifully plated were not particularly memorable but the main dishes were really balanced both in flavor and texture. The pan seared scallops were the perfect combination of richness and flavor, while the Sedani (their homemade Bolognese) with thinly sliced shallots, (what I tasted) garlic and delicate crumble of beef was both fatty and acidic with the pasta cooked just al dente.  Service was what you’d expect in a restaurant of this caliber, friendly, but not helicoptering around you, plates arrived relatively quickly but they did not ask us if we wanted to main served and we waited a while because we had a few half eaten starters still on the table.  Space is airy but still warm, the ideal mix of casual and upmarket, I can see this being an ideal first date, though the higher ceilings and wood fixtures did the sound a bit so be expected to yell a little across the table. Bar tables would probably be better for a twosome. Cozy and welcoming.  Only minus on the stars because one of the two bathrooms has no hook or table to place personals, pretty sure the gals in Bushwick still carry bags. Toilet paper super thin :p wouldn’t ordinarily mention it but I eat in a range of all restaurants and these pluses are what you would expect at a restaurant like this.

This is literally my favorite restaurant, not just in Brooklyn but anywhere. I've been to Faro probably 12 or 15 times, on dates, with friends, with family, once or twice by myself. Chef Kevin Adey and his wife/co-owner Deb are absolutely fantastic, super sweet and unassuming, very welcoming, which is rare for a trendy Michelin-starred spot. More importantly, the food is unbelievably good. I'm old school Italian from the New York area, so I tend to be pretty traditional when it comes to pasta. But Chef Kevin is a freaking genius, and he's able to blend old tradition and contemporary innovation and creativity in a way that is extremely difficult to pull of. He'll make some obscure but delicious form of hand-made fresh pasta that dates back hundreds of years to some region of Italy, and then combine it with something super modern, and marry the old and the new in a way you would never expect. I can't say enough about this place, it's an absolute must-try. I highly recommend the tasting menu, you get to sit up at the kitchen and watch them make everything, and Chef Kevin will tell you about every dish and often the history behind what he's doing. God I love this place.

Christmas Eve dinner at Faro - very creative menu with 6 courses featuring different kinds of "fish". Well balanced menu with a very strong start. Fluke is delightfully sweet and the slight sourness from apple plus the creaminess from avocado made a good combo. Crab mixed well with cauliflower purée while squid ink vinaigrette added more savory. Fazzoletti was full of egg flavor, pairing with garlic sauce became a solid wholesome dish. However, the main courses are less impressive compared to the appetizers. The lobster, though very tender, didn't feel like a cohesive dish with the cannelini beans and the muscle did not add much on top, and the three different ingredients with 3 different temperature made the dish more far apart. The cod felt a bit overcooked, while the crispy outside was nice, the inside was not as tender and juicy as I expected from cod, and I didn't taste much of the sweetness from cod either. Turtle chocolate tart pulled the meal back a bit by its light and gooey caramel wrapped in dark chocolate and walnuts, topped with fluffy vanilla cream. Overall a good meal with some areas of improvement.  Last note, Faro's pasta game is really strong, will definitely want to try more of their pasta dishes in the future.

Lastly, we got the buttacini, and the fowl meal pasta, both of which were perfect. 3 stars because of the hyped expectations, and the misses on half the plates.

Great food especially for dinner. You won't go wrong with anything in the menu. The staff is friendly and quick. I recommend sitting at kitchen so you can see all the mazing dishes being whipped up. I don't recommend any desserts from here. They were unmoving. Find another spot to finish the night. You won't be able to get a coffee at the end of the night. The food is A+
Faro is one of those rare gems of a place where you're sure you haven't tried enough of the menu.  Price is $$$ Taste is A  Would recommend to anyone looking for a special time.

Pasta dishes are great. I am only leaving 3 stars because the food was inconsistent.  If you are into cabbage definitely try the Caraflex Cabbage, the Duck Liver Mousse was also tasty.  We tried 2 pasta dishes. The ricotta gnocchi had layered flavors and was a good dish overall. I do not recommend the fazzoletti. I thought this dish would be good because it has buratta and a pork ragu but it lacked salt and other flavor.  New York Strip was ok. Duck entree was not impressive.  Bread and butter was good but keep in mind they charge $6 for a roll.  Gin cocktail was good but very sweet. After drinking 3 I was barely buzzed.
Really, really good. Elegant and refined, this tucked away gem delivers.
Small portions and meh desserts
Amazing pasta. Service is a bit brisk, and we would have appreciated a slower pace.
Food was great.  Server was friendly and knowledgeable and offered suggestions on food and wine.
Terrible service. Meh food. Many other restaurants in NYC and Brooklyn that are more deserving of Michelin status.

Faro has INCREDIBLE food. Their menu changes constantly, but that’s ok because no matter what you pick, it’s always absolutely and magnificently delicious. I live walking distance from the restaurant, so I’ve eaten there several times, and I’ve never been disappointed.  Their seafood pasta always tastes fresh, their service is always top-notch, and the environment never feels stuffy or elitist. This is, hands-down, one of the best Italian restaurants in all off New York.  I do have to mention, however, that when it comes to their after-dinner coffee, the espressos are definitely not the greatest. Still, it doesn’t really matter because their food makes up for it a hundred times over.

Faro provided a beyond expectations dining experience from the second we walked in the door. I immediately appreciated the open and inviting atmosphere with the kitchen proudly on display and open to be observed in the back of the restaurant. I got the squid ink pasta with broiled octopus in top and it was a phenomenal dish, especially for the price of $16 dollars. Service was excellent and as was the food. I will definitely be coming back to this spot with friends and family and there's a good reason why this spot has earned a Michelin star.

This place is a hidden treasure in Brooklyn! The pastas were our of this world. So tasty! It is a great not-expensive option to surprise someone for a special occasion. I love that they let you bring your own bottle of wine for a reasonable corkage fee.

This place is one of my favorite places to dine in Brooklyn. The creativity, taste and an homage to traditional culinary techniques blend harmoniously in the food served at this place. Excellent service and reasonably priced for the experience you get.
Unbelievable pasta!

The service was amazing. I loved the atmosphere. Staff was friendly and on top of tending to their tables, the food came out looking amazing and was extremely delicious! And desert topped it off perfectly. Excellent experience and would definitely visit again.
Delicious pastas and a great selection of natural wines.
Amazing starters
Loved it, everything amazing!
Were I a poet this review would reflect the majesty of our meal.
Fantastic experience!  Delicious beyond words!

Food was good not great. Portions were small, sad!  Kinda like a roller coaster at 6flags, wait ina really long line for something that you think is gonna be great but are let down.  Bread was fantastic  Service horrible, didnt clear dishes had to ask them, after servers walked by multiple times eyeing table and not doing anything  Multiple courses came out cold, pasta rigatoni and duck dishes were cold.  They gave us the pumpkin mouse on the house wasnt bad.
A bit pricey but the food is delicious.
Top 5 best Italian restaurant in NYC . Without doubt
(Translated by Google) Flavor perfect, portions small :)  (Original) Lezzet mükemmel, porsiyonlar küçük :)

Went for a birthday dinner and food was ok (not great) and expensive for what it was.  Hospitality was second rate - they asked you if the food was ok, but they don't really care.  We left two courses with more than half left on our plate, and they never asked us what was wrong with them.  The bar stools for the prix fixe  dinner were incredibly uncomfortable - it cut circulation to the legs after a while.  We started to stand and eat our dessert, but again, no one asked us what was wrong.  A big negative when it comes to hospitality.  We ordered the prix fixe and some dishes were creative, but the pasta itself tasted fine, nothing special.  Some dishes were too bland or the pasta was not especially appetizing (like one dish where it was baked in rectangles and tasted like firm polenta mush).

Just-okay pricey dishes to share in an open, industrial space that err more on the casual side (and not in any interesting way). The starter/veggie dishes were good. While the pasta is supposed to be fresh and made in house, it was too firm (tougher than al dente) in 2/3 pasta dishes we had. Our server was attentive although they overlooked the little detail I requested in the reservation ("It's my friend's birthday—please add a candle to dessert or something"). No veg option for the tasting menu.

Update 10 days after being there for the first time 5 to 2 stars : 10.24.2017 Was not as good and fresh as the first time. Go once, its great. not twice.  10.14.2014 This place is amazing! Food is awesome and wine too, service is very nice ! We will come back very soon for sure <3
Food is good, nice selection of red wine and amari. Food portions are a bit too small and over priced but the place is cozy and nice. Good for a chill date with friends
delicious!!!
Overall experience wad outstanding!
Try the Sweet Potato pasta- is incredible. Wish they had vegan options but still worth the visit.
Incredible pasta. A fine dining experience at an affordable price.
Amazing food, unique cocktails, and the most attentive staff. The experience would be hard to beat even in NYC.
Host was very cold.
Excellent chef
Gorgeous, delectable - a revelation

Faro is delicious. The space is really loud and a bit stark in terms of design but we loved the food.  Delicious and innovative.  Friendly service and lots of close bars nearby - perfect for a little bushwick exploration.
If you get a chance to do a chef's table dinner! DO IT! Everything was amazing!

Excellent dinner. Space is a bit cavernous and spare, nice in the summer, but may feel a little chilly in the winter. Open space also made it a bit loud even when all tables not full. All of the staff were very friendly and attentive
Everything was really delicious, including cocktails and wine.
Best meal I've ever had! Just wow...
Amazing as always
Faro is the best. Awesome food, especially the pasta, great service and great wine selection.
very solid meal. nothing really blew us away, but there was nothing to complain about either, and the squid ink pasta was very, very good.
Best fine dining in bushwick. Amazing pasta. Super fresh.
This place is perfect!
Great food, excellent service, moderate price.
It wasn't bad at all but not what you expect from a 1 star Michelin. We had duck tortellini and skirt steak with spaghetti. Good but I won't come again.
No crowds on a Tuesday evening, relaxed atmosphere and the food was quite memorable, delicious.
Delicious food, great wine list, and very good service

Food is inconsistent. Dishes take a very long time to arrive. We came here because we work right around the corner and heard this restaurant had a Michelin star. Don't think they deserve it yet. Service was a little cold.  The steak tartare and beets were our appetizer. They were extremely salty despite the rave reviews. Pastas were creative and definitely the best things on the menu. Plenty of options but we ordered the Bucantini twice and one was definitely better than the other.

What I love about Bushwick, Brooklyn  it's eclectic.  So Faro is a perfect pair with our Flare.  It's not the run of the mill typical Italian dish.  It's fantastic high quality with perfect proportions.  Welcome to Bushwick and I hope you great success!
Great food, classic style
Yass.
Amazing takes on Italian classics. You can usually find space at the bar and the service there is great.

Definitely a nice space! If you're tired of Bushwick bars where you can't breathe, this will be a refreshing stop. Plenty of open space for their tables and bar, and friendly staff. Food was heavy yet amazing, and their wines are well priced.
Food was good (not everything though) but I didn't quite enjoy the dinner. Felt pretentious and a bit empty of soul and character...
Not only were the pasta dishes great,  the scallops,  and duck were also amazing!
Good food and great service.
Great food and great service.
Delicious and interesting pasta
Fantastic food: perfect flavor pairings and delicious home made pastas. Drinks are amazing as well. Will be back.
Well deserving of their Michelin star, really exceptional food, and the service is some of the best you'll ever experience.
If you're willing to spend the money, it's worth EVERY penny- simply one of the best meals I've ever had in NYC, in over 7 years.
Love this place! Had one of the best meals of the year here back  in April and now we are back for the NYE pre fix.
Food is always interning and exiting - drinks are fun and inventive. Highly recommended

I'm rather confused by all of the rave reviews and Faro's recent award of a Michelin star (which I think is very undeserved).  The Mackerel Crudo and the Petite Lettuces were both very uninteresting and not very flavorful, and while I enjoyed the Foie Gras (even with the toast that was served burnt) and the Roasted Beets, neither were above average in terms of taste or creativity.  Of the five pastas I sampled, one was completely inedible and incredibly fishy (the Squid Ink Rigatoni), another was disliked by the entire table (the Strangelopretti) and the Agnolotti was fine, but not good and I wouldn't order it again.  We did all like the Gnochetti (which only comes in an appetizer sized portion) and the Scarpinocc, but enjoying 2 out of 5 pasta dishes are not good odds for a Michelin star restaurant.  We also ordered the Scallops, which were also fine, but felt like something I can replicate at home and were not impressive, and the Bread and Butter, which were not worth paying for and I had to chase someone down to bring the butter because the server only brought is the bread.  I wouldn't recommend traveling into Bushwick for what turned out to be a mediocre meal, at best.
The food is generally pretty good, but it's rather inconsistent. Doesn't deserve a Michelin star by any means.
See pictures uploaded. Almost everything was fantastic including the staff. However, Desert was below average. Bland bread pudding & chocolate cake. I will go back.
Farm to table , mills their own grains bakes their own bread makes their own exceptional pasta the bushwick bomber, Faro is the epitome of culinary excellence in the neighborhood.
The place is modern, and cozy with mood lighting. The menu has exotic handmade pasta dishes. The plates are small, but packed with flavor. Perfect for romantic date.
Perfect food. Incredible staff. Yummmmmm
This is the best dinning experience in Brooklyn or maybe even in NYC. The pasta, the wine, the people, the vibe... The SAUCE!!!

A lovely place for an excellent meal. The staff is tremendously attentive and the food, sublime. This evening I enjoyed the partridge appetizer special and it was amazing. Paired with an expertly built cocktail, it's a rough life...
Great farm to table food

I heard amazing things about this place, and to be sure, the food is good. But I don't think I can ever go back or my bank account will hate me. I live in the area so it's not like I'm a stranger to expensive meals, but for what it is, I just can't justify returning. If money is no object, go for it.

I find myself thinking about my dinner at faro even days later. Food was unreal. Noodles tasted incredibly fresh- a bowl of plain spaghetti would have been worth 4 stars. Some of the dishes sounded a little odd but both my dinner and my girlfriend's were fan-frickin-tastic.  Neat selection of local beers and a good wine selection.  Interior was minimalist, bright and clean with an open kitchen. Hardwood and high ceilings with white walls and stacks of fire wood.
Sweet Jesus I never hype places but the veal ragu at Faro has me feeling emotional.

I ate here shortly after they opened during Bushwick Open Studios and it was obvious that they were overwhelmed. We waited about an hour for a table enjoying some cocktails. When it came time to order, I ordered the gluten free pasta. 20 minutes later I was told they chef miscounted and there was no pasta left. So I changed my order and another 20 minutes later my filet mignon was served. The waitress was really apologetic the whole time. The steak was good and the other meals ordered were as well. The bill came and the waitress informed me that my meal would be free including the beer. She also brought me some uncooked pasta to bring home saying that he chef had freshly made it and wanted me to try it. Best customer service I've experienced at a restaurant. I never complained or asked for anything, they just did it. I would definitely go back.

One of the best culinary experiences I've had, but with reasonable prices--no entree over $25 and pastas are around $15. I've eaten at many Michelin Star restaurants in NYC and this is right up there. We sat at the chef's table and it very cool to see the chefs cooking and everything being prepared. The decor inside is very Brooklyn and pretty awesome; elegant, relaxed and classy all at the same time.. The bread is cooked in this wood fired oven and served to you with their homemade butter when it first comes out, definitely some of the best ever. Our main courses were the pork special that night (amazing) and octopus (so good and fresh!). We started with the tomato, fresh mozzarella and beet salad which is much more elegant than it sounds; care was taken with peeling the vegetables and it was so tasty and different..We also had a cavatelli with summer truffles as an in-between--kind of like a super fancy freshly made mac on cheese on crack (but with truffles lol). For dessert we had chocolate olive oil cake with some ice cream on top and arugula sorbet--sounds and tasted different than anything I've ever had, but it was legit. Can't wait to continue going back!
Delicious and gorgeous.
Some of the best pasta dishes I've had. Absolutely awesome environment and a fantastic staff. A must if you're in Bushwick.

Ate here with my daughter who lives in Brooklyn- was really impressed. The vibe is simple and elegant but the food complex and delicious. We tried a bit of everything, but my favorite was the steak tartare appetizer and the cod entree.  The wine was not overly expensive and the food prices consistent with the quality. A great find!

Absolutely delicious. The porridge was divine, the whiskey sours were on point, and the service was incredible. Establishment is modern but modest, the music playlist is awesome and the overall experience was wonderful! Definitely check this spot out
THIS IS MY FAVORITE PLACE TO DINE IN BUSHWICK. THE HOMEMADE PASTA, AND THE LOVE PUT IN THE FOOD IS SO SPECIAL. THE OWNERS ARE ONE OF A KIND AMAZING PEEPS!

Came here with a friend without a reso. They fit us in at the back counter by the kitchen. Everyone that worked there was so lovely and gave honest descriptions of the dishes they love and why. The food was exquisite and the head chef gave us some sort of chilled pudding with bacon on top which I never would have ordered for myself, but found that I enjoyed it and will get it next time I'm there. If you're in that area or looking for a great dining experience this place is a MUST!!!

We had a very comfortable experience.  The bar tender was friendly.  The ambiance was warm but simple. The drinks we ordered was very well made. The real reason to rave about this place is the absolute deliciousness of the food!! I was nothing less than impressed, and left with a full belly.

Came here for a late dinner for 2, didn't have a reservation and it was full but are at the bar. Delicious food, creatively prepared, good cocktails, informative and friendly wait staff. A great experience, would definitely return.
Nolte rec
Great ingredients, dishes are simple but done perfectly, only negative is that's extremely noisy space.
Large, open space.  Seasonal, local and organic menu.  Definitely a top 5 Williamsburg/Bushwick destination
Good looking cooks

Set on a block that's rather quiet, but just down the street from the train,  Faro stands out as a clean, open space with killer dishes. The beets were a standout item along with the scallops, both appetizers and perfectly-sized. Service is friendly and attentive. Decor is simple,  with exposed brick and blonde wood throughout. A major bonus is the open kitchen and brick oven, complete with seating so you can watch the magic happen. I'll definitely return for what I hear is absolutely delicious pizza and another The New Bushwick Buck, a delightfully fresh ginger and vodka cocktail.

Seasonal, inventive fare — not your standard Italian. Cocktails are delicious and refreshing (try the Blackberry Bramble). Scallops were standout. Panna cotta was also excellent. Service is pleasant and accommodating. Though open and airy, the space can be quite loud.

I don't normally stray too far from the city, but this place is worth a visit. The venue boasts a grand rustic bar with delicious cocktails.  Food was delicious. I, along with friends, enjoyed five courses -- roasted beet, duck, porridge, seared scallops, and panna cotta.  Ambience was nice. It's noisier than I would have liked, but it was a festive evening.

A hidden gem surrounded by Bushwick Street Art. The warehouse converted to restaurant allows for a community dining feel. The food is delicious and the staff make you feel at home. My drink of choice was the Blackberry Bramble. I look forward to going back again soon!

It was a pleasant surprise to discover this gem in the Bushwick neighborhood. The venue is quite spacious with a roomy bar area - this place can definitely accommodate large groups with ease. Food here is superb with fine-dining portion size. Their roasted beet starter, scallop dish and duck entree are excellent and very reasonably priced (they also make their pasta here in-house)! Noise level tend to be high given its rustic decor and loft ceiling.  Though it's a bit far out, it certainly is worth a visit!

Faro is ideal for large groups. It has a festive atmosphere that's perfect for hanging with college buddies, co-workers or friends visiting from out of town. This place is off the beaten path and has incredible food - get the duck! I'll be going back for seconds.
Fantastic and beautifully plated dishes with fresh local ingredients made for one of my favorite dining experiences in this city. I'd recommend making a special trip to Bushwick to experience Faro

Take a break from street art spotting in Bushwick and step inside this glass fronted trendy "Italian" spot heating up Brooklyn's foodie scene. While the restaurant feels a bit out of place along the street, it's conveniently located steps from an L train entrance and absolutely worth the trip. High celings, simple wooden tables and chairs, and minimal-to-no-decor keep the focus on the fantastic dishes being served out of a kitchen so open it might as well be seated at a table. The duck was so good I would bring anyone who claims they don't like the fowl in and dare them to try and dislike it. The almond corn crumble, Panna Cotta and strawberry dessert though is what really rang my bell, but all of the dishes were well balanced, well portioned, and very pleasing to the palate.
